         »CL4:Constructed by Wade 

»CL8:Introduction
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL0:After the positive feedback concerning
my original article, Writers on
Writers (released in Showtime 14), I
decided to complete this belated
follow-up: Writers on Magazines. 

In the same vein as its predecessor,
this article takes the views of those
associated with the subject matter
(i.e. diskmags) with the intention of
giving a somewhat more educated
response.
       »PIC:Darklight.+EC_07.iff»









Regretfully, since this article was
conceived there has been a major
decline in the amount of disk
magazines released on the Amiga scene.
Nonetheless, I have decided to
complete this article in the hope that
it may inspire those who once played a
role in this essential aspect of scene
life. 
»CL8:The Writer's critique »CL9:--------------->
»CL4:SEENPOINT by Scoopex
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL1:Wade writes:»CL0: It resides at number 1 in
most charts, and deservingly so. In
terms of appearance, I believe it took
a step backwards over the years. It's
murky colour and smeared panels are
far from appealing. However, what it
misses in design, it makes up for with
its quality content. Hard hitting
facts, scoops and even libel; highly
proficient language skills and tough
quality control, Seenpoint has the lot
and flaunts it better than any other
mag existing today.
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL3:Sane writes:»CL2: Even though I am a member
of the staff of this mag, I want to
say one thing: Seenpoint has by far
the best and most skilled staff.
»CL1:Bytebreaker writes:»CL0:
Pleasant for eye and ear.
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL5:Shade writes:»CL4: Has become better with
time. With Sane and Fishwave comes
intrigue, interest and lies, something
that naturally attracts the attention
of the readers. A lot of bad things'
been said about the way journalism is
conducted in this magazine, but that
does not mean it's not interesting. By
loading Seenpoint you will always find
something you want to read. If it's
true or not, that's another story :)
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL8:Curt Cool writes:
»CL7:The best mag these days. Provocative,
interesting and not released too
often. Always caters for quality
articles by the three main editors.
»CL4:TRASHCAN by Network
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL1:Wade writes:
»CL0:Fantastic design and graphics, with
that oldschool atmosphere. The article
content varies so much, from excellent
to extremely poor. It would make
faster progress if cut down, to a pack
mag for example, dedicated to its most
prominent articles.
