»CL4:GENERATION by Artwork
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL1:Wade writes:
»CL0:The panel graphics are quite
extraordinary and the cliparts are
sufficient, but the small font and
plain backdrop make it quite
unpleasant on the eyes. It's content
has had its ups and downs. Issues
leading up to 25b were outstanding,
pushing it to a well deserved spot in
the charts. 25b onwards, the magazine
became little more than a corporate
billboard containing way too much in
the way of outside support and
pre-released material in the form of
party reports, results, news group
information and commercial banter. Its
death was a little overdue.

»CL3:Sane writes:
»CL2:Although it featured MANY
non-interesting articles it was for me
the most professional magazine in the
entire history of the Scene. Rokdee as
mained, what can go wrong?
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL5:Ghandy writes:
»CL4:A good mag for sure! Is there any
chance that Rokdazone will continue
after he`s now so busy with 1000 other
things? (Tiefsee Music Productions,
University, Job as Webdesigner etc.) I
really hope it!
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL7:Bytebreaker writes:
»CL6:The GUI hasn't changed much throughout
the years. Nevertheless it is easy to
handle and that's the main point.

