»CL4:ROM by Essence
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL1:Wade writes:

»CL0:Undoubtedly one of the greatest
magazines of the scene. Its interface
is still outstanding compared to
today's standards; a non aga magazine
that scrolls, multitasks and displays
colourful cliparts; a feat that no one
has been able to match since, despite
AGA and fastmem assistance. Aside from
its fantastic design and code, Rom was
the father of professional scene
writing, taking inspiration from real
life media and journalism. Rom set a
standard for other magazines to aspire
to. 


»CL3:Sane writes:
»CL2:Best design until now! Great music and
gfx that really dominated; a joy for
your ears and eyes. The articles were
too long and too boring though.
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL5:Ghandy writes:
»CL4:Perfect design, still the best code of
the Scene (nobody will ever manage to
beat Touchstone!) , fantastic modules
& brilliant titlepics. But the
contents were always disapointing for
me. What`s in here for me to read, I
asked myself.. nothing really
embrassing to read. 
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL7:Bytebreaker writes:
»CL6:Rest in peace. You were not only
pretty, you were even functional.

