»CL4:RETRO by Instinct
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL1:Wade writes:»CL0: To repeat the words of
the entire scene, Retro's design is
terrible. This is somewhat due to
palette restrictions and lacking
features. However, the minimalistic
surroundings serve their purpose,
despite its Amos engine. In terms of
articles, it got off to a bad start
with its joke sections and outright
infantile nature. By issue 3 things
began to look up and by issue 4, Retro
was deservingly among the scene's
leading diskmags. 
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL3:Shade writes: »CL2: I hate the layout.
Makes me feel I am reading a txt file.
