»CL7:Wade writes:»CL8: The panel graphics are
very nice as is the whole design, yet
the code seems to be a falling point,
requiring fastmem and containing heaps
of bugs and glitches. Judging on its
content, Phoenix's appears to follow
in the footsteps of Grapevine and the
lesser known The Word; a public forum
for anyone who wishes to contribute,
scener or non scener. A nice idea in
theory, but Phoenix (as with other
mags of this type) is overrun with a
childish content such as jokes and
entertainment coverage; like written
conversations from the local pub. When
one can obtain researched information
from television, the internet, paper
magazines or their local library,
Phoenix appears surplus in the
diskmag community.
»CL4:PHOENIX by Giants (continued)
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL1:Sane writes:

»CL0:Nice but not extremely good. Now it
needs fastmem and that -as said- sucks
deep!

