»CL4:JURASSIC PACK by Gods
»CL9:--------------------------------------
»CL1:Wade writes:

»CL0:Its design worked well for its initial
issues, but as time passed, it grew
outdated. Sadly, it's attempts to
improve the code was a complete
disaster, demonstrating no visual
advantages for its extended memory
requirement. While the interface
remains unchanged, the magazine itself
has evolved - perhaps a little too
much for one man (Ghandy) to handle
alone, despite his laborious efforts.
The result of its size increase comes
in the form of excessive fillers and
largely outdated articles - sometimes
upto and over a year old. Jurassic
Pack could keep a scener entertained
for hours, with a varied content
covering aspects of the demo scene,
crack scene, the Amiga and even the
PC, but often fails to maintain the
pace of scene events. 



»CL9:--------------------------------------



»CL3:Sane writes:
»CL2:
This must be the first low budget
"magazine" which made it into the
charts and that's great! The "mag" is
entertaining but not skilled. The last
issue was rushed and therefore it
sucked.


